arger loans may offer another means of support, but collaboration between formal microfinance institutions or NGOs and refugee-led groups must reinforce rather than devalue the networks of trust that contribute to grassroots savings and loan groups’ success. © 2020 The Authors. Development Policy Review published by John Wiley & Sons Ltd on behalf of Overseas Development Institute
